SheTrades Workshop returns with a workshop titled “Preparing For The Export Market.” The workshop will take place at the Shehu Musa Yaradua Centre, Central District on the 20th of March, 2019. Focused on the Textiles and Apparel sector, finished beauty products and IT&BPO sectors, the event aims to give the project stakeholders and participants an overview of the programme and its goals and activities as well as hearing from participants about the key issues and challenges they face in accessing international markets. The sectors to be addressed at the Workshop include IT&BPO, Textiles and Apparel and Finished Shea Beauty Products. To participate, registered members should log onto SheTrades in the Commonwealth account; go through the Capacity Building Tab on top of your homepage and click on the link to register next to “Workshop in Nigeria.”